<h1>WELCOME TO  vMic - THE VIRTUAL MICROSCOPE</h1>

<p>
vMic enables you to interactively explore light-microscopic samples with your 
webbrowser as with a real microscope. Slides of up to 40mm by 25mm are captured 
at 400x with maximum optical quality. 
This site is public and there is no registration required.</p>

<p><strong>Attention: </strong><br />
No further slides will be added to this project. For much more slides and courses with a new webviewer visit <a href="http://pathorama.ch/" target="outofvmic">PATHORAMA</a>. However, the slides and courses in vMic are not available in the newer vSlides and vCollections. So you might have a closer look on both .. <br /><br /> </p>

<p>vMic features Virtual Slides in the following sections:</p>
<h2>PATHOLOGY</h2>
<p> This section comprises histopathologic slides from various fields 
  of pathology and a collection of slide seminars. <a href="patho/index.html">Go there...</a> </p>

<h2>ORALHISTOLOGY</h2>
<p>A complete course addressing students of dentistry. <a href="http://oralhisto.unibas.ch" >Go there...</a> </p>
<h2>
MINERALOGY</h2>
<p>This section demonstrates vMic's power for non-medical applications. <a href="mineral/index.html">Go there...</a> </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>We appreciate your feedback!<br />
  <em>Katharina &amp; Dieter Glatz-Krieger</em></p>
